==English==
===Etymology===
From old French ''verbe'', from Latin ''[[verbum]]'' word, from Indo-European *''wer-''

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /vɜː(r)b/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /v3:(r)b/

===Noun===
'''verb''' (''plural'' '''verbs''')

<!--Are these two distinct definitions, or two ways of describing the same thing?-->
# a word that serves as the [[predicate]] of a [[sentence]]
# a content word that denotes an action or a state

